## Usage\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
import \{\par
  InputGroup,\par
  InputGroupAddon,\par
  InputGroupButton,\par
  InputGroupInput,\par
  InputGroupText,\par
  InputGroupTextarea,\par
\} from "@/components/ui/input-group"\par
```\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
<InputGroup>\par
  <InputGroupInput placeholder="Search..." />\par
  <InputGroupAddon>\par
    <SearchIcon />\par
  </InputGroupAddon>\par
</InputGroup>\par
```\par
\par
## Composition\par
\par
Use the following composition to build an `InputGroup`:\par
\par
```text\par
InputGroup\par
\f1\u9500?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  InputGroupInput or InputGroupTextarea\par
\f1\u9500?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  InputGroupAddon\par
\f1\u9500?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  InputGroupButton\par
\f1\u9492?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  InputGroupText\par
```\par
\par
## Align\par
\par
Use the `align` prop on `InputGroupAddon` to position the addon relative to the input.\par
\par
<Callout>\par
  For proper focus management, `InputGroupAddon` should always be placed after\par
  `InputGroupInput` or `InputGroupTextarea` in the DOM. Use the `align` prop to\par
  visually position the addon.\par
</Callout>\par
\par
### inline-start\par
\par
Use `align="inline-start"` to position the addon at the start of the input. This is the default.\par
\par
<ComponentPreview\par
  styleName="radix-nova"\par
  name="input-group-inline-start"\par
  previewClassName="h-48"\par
/>\par
\par
### inline-end\par
\par
Use `align="inline-end"` to position the addon at the end of the input.\par
\par
<ComponentPreview\par
  styleName="radix-nova"\par
  name="input-group-inline-end"\par
  previewClassName="h-48"\par
/>\par
\par
### block-start\par
\par
Use `align="block-start"` to position the addon above the input.\par
\par
<ComponentPreview\par
  styleName="radix-nova"\par
  name="input-group-block-start"\par
  previewClassName="h-96"\par
/>\par
\par
### block-end\par
\par
Use `align="block-end"` to position the addon below the input.\par
\par
<ComponentPreview\par
  styleName="radix-nova"\par
  name="input-group-block-end"\par
  previewClassName="h-[26rem]"\par
/>\par
