## API Reference\par
\par
### InputGroup\par
\par
The main component that wraps inputs and addons.\par
\par
| Prop        | Type     | Default |\par
| ----------- | -------- | ------- |\par
| `className` | `string` |         |\par
\par
```tsx\par
<InputGroup>\par
  <InputGroupInput />\par
  <InputGroupAddon />\par
</InputGroup>\par
```\par
\par
### InputGroupAddon\par
\par
Displays icons, text, buttons, or other content alongside inputs.\par
\par
<Callout icon=\{<IconInfoCircle />\} title="Focus Navigation">\par
  For proper focus navigation, the `InputGroupAddon` component should be placed\par
  after the input. Set the `align` prop to position the addon.\par
</Callout>\par
\par
| Prop        | Type                                                             | Default          |\par
| ----------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------- |\par
| `align`     | `"inline-start" \\| "inline-end" \\| "block-start" \\| "block-end"` | `"inline-start"` |\par
| `className` | `string`                                                         |                  |\par
\par
```tsx\par
<InputGroupAddon align="inline-end">\par
  <SearchIcon />\par
</InputGroupAddon>\par
```\par
\par
**For `<InputGroupInput />`, use the `inline-start` or `inline-end` alignment. For `<InputGroupTextarea />`, use the `block-start` or `block-end` alignment.**\par
\par
The `InputGroupAddon` component can have multiple `InputGroupButton` components and icons.\par
\par
```tsx\par
<InputGroupAddon>\par
  <InputGroupButton>Button</InputGroupButton>\par
  <InputGroupButton>Button</InputGroupButton>\par
</InputGroupAddon>\par
```\par
\par
### InputGroupButton\par
\par
Displays buttons within input groups.\par
\par
| Prop        | Type                                                                          | Default   |\par
| ----------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------- |\par
| `size`      | `"xs" \\| "icon-xs" \\| "sm" \\| "icon-sm"`                                      | `"xs"`    |\par
| `variant`   | `"default" \\| "destructive" \\| "outline" \\| "secondary" \\| "ghost" \\| "link"` | `"ghost"` |\par
| `className` | `string`                                                                      |           |\par
\par
```tsx\par
<InputGroupButton>Button</InputGroupButton>\par
<InputGroupButton size="icon-xs" aria-label="Copy">\par
  <CopyIcon />\par
</InputGroupButton>\par
```\par
\par
### InputGroupInput\par
\par
Replacement for `<Input />` when building input groups. This component has the input group styles pre-applied and uses the unified `data-slot="input-group-control"` for focus state handling.\par
\par
| Prop        | Type     | Default |\par
| ----------- | -------- | ------- |\par
| `className` | `string` |         |\par
\par
All other props are passed through to the underlying `<Input />` component.\par
\par
```tsx\par
<InputGroup>\par
  <InputGroupInput placeholder="Enter text..." />\par
  <InputGroupAddon>\par
    <SearchIcon />\par
  </InputGroupAddon>\par
</InputGroup>\par
```\par
\par
### InputGroupTextarea\par
\par
Replacement for `<Textarea />` when building input groups. This component has the textarea group styles pre-applied and uses the unified `data-slot="input-group-control"` for focus state handling.\par
\par
| Prop        | Type     | Default |\par
| ----------- | -------- | ------- |\par
| `className` | `string` |         |\par
\par
All other props are passed through to the underlying `<Textarea />` component.\par
\par
```tsx\par
<InputGroup>\par
  <InputGroupTextarea placeholder="Enter message..." />\par
  <InputGroupAddon align="block-end">\par
    <InputGroupButton>Send</InputGroupButton>\par
  </InputGroupAddon>\par
</InputGroup>\par
```\par
